H0.text: An organ is the term that best identifies the parts of the body that carry out the function of digestion, a process that begins in the mouth and involves many different body parts.

H1.text: An organism is the term that best identifies the parts of the body that carry out the function of digestion, a process in humans that begins in the mouth and involves many different parts of the body.

H2.text: A system is the term that best identifies the parts of the body that carry out digestion, a process that begins in the mouth and involves many different parts of the human body.

H3.text: A tissue is the part of the body that carries out the function of digestion, a process that in humans begins in the mouth and involves many different body parts.

A4.text: The human digestive system consists of the gastrointestinal tract plus the accessory organs of digestion (the tongue, salivary glands, pancreas, liver, and gallbladder).

A5.text: The largest structure of the digestive system is the GI tract.
